  "texts": [
    "The rising concerns about digital ageism highlight the pressing need for further research and policy interventions to address the potential biases and discriminatory practices that may affect older adults in the digital era [13][14][15].",
    "Recent studies have demonstrated instances of digital ageism, emphasizing the urgency of designing and deploying technologically inclusive solutions to ensure equitable treatment and opportunities for individuals of all ages [16].",
    "The exclusion of older adults from the development of digital technologies has been previously researched [15,17,18] and can manifest in many ways.",
    "Older adults may not be adequately represented in training and testing data for ML models, resulting in models with reduced accuracy for older adult data and being vulnerable to multiple intersecting disadvantages [19].",
    "For example, older adults who live in long-term care homes may have limited access to the internet and may be excluded from technological advances [20]."
  ],
